question: What is the name of near-Earth object identified to be the Surveyor 2 Centaur rocket booster?
explanation: NASA has confirmed that 2020 SO which is a near-Earth object identified to be the Surveyor 2 Centaur rocket booster assisted lift in the spacecraft towards the moon in 1996. It was discovered by the Pan-STARRS1 survey at the Haleakala Observatory.
